<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - TURBOCHARGER - Removal - High
        Torque Wastegated Turbocharger
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="5">
        <title>High Torque Wastegated Turbocharger</title>
        <figure id="f1200217" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figEG7/EG7404.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Removing the Road Draft Tube</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Road Draft Tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Road Draft Tube Mounting Bolts</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankcase Breather</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Air Inlet Elbow</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen the hose clamp and disconnect the road draft tube from the crankcase breather.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the road draft tube mounting bolts from the crankcase. Remove the tube.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen the air inlet elbow clamp and remove air inlet elbow from the turbocharger.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200219" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg9/EG9128.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                     scalefitheight="472px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Removing the Charge Air Cooling Tube/Crossover Pipe Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crossover Pipe</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Charge Air Cooling Tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Hose Clamps</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Manifold Hoses</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Compressor Outlet Seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Compressor Outlet Clamp</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the charging air cooling tube/crossover pipe assembly as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Loosen the four hose clamps (two per side) and remove the two manifold hoses that are
                    secured to the air intake covers.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Loosen the turbocharger compressor outlet clamp that secures the charge air cooling tube
                    to the turbocharger compressor housing.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the charge air cooling tube/crossover pipe assembly from the engine.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the turbocharger compressor outlet seal from the compressor housing.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place protective caps onto the air intake manifolds.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200221" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg6/EG6430.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Turbocharger Disconnect Points</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Inlet Clamp</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Inlet Adapter</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Mounting Bolt (2)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen the exhaust inlet clamp. Disconnect the exhaust inlet adapter and remove the seal.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the two bolts that secure the turbocharger to the pedestal. Remove the turbocharger
                from the pedestal.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the four bolts that secure the pedestal to the crankcase. Remove the pedestal.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200222" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3303.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                     scalefitheight="472px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Turbocharger Oil Supply and Oil Drain Ports</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Supply O-Ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Drain O-Ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger Mounting Pad</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard the two O-rings located on the turbocharger mounting pad.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard the oil supply O-ring and oil drain O-ring located on the underside of
                the turbocharger or the top of the pedestal.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200223" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg6/EG6414.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Turbocharger Exhaust Tube Mounting Hardware (Right Side Shown)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Right Exhaust Tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Tube Mounting Nut</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Right Exhaust Manifold</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Exhaust Tube Mounting Bolt</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the exhaust tube mounting hardware at the left and right exhaust manifolds.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the turbocharger exhaust tube assembly from the engine.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cap all openings on the turbocharger assembly. If plastic caps are not available, use duct
                tape to cover openings.
            </para>
        </step1>
